Wombo Definition WOMBO is the world's best Al-powered lip sync app

How to use Wombo to make a photo lip-sync to a
song Press the green W icon below your picture â€“ or if you've changed your mind, press back and try again.8. Now it's time to choose your tune. The 18
available songs span a wide range of genres and eras, so there's likely to be at least one you're happy
with. Plus, Benkhin says he plans to expand the options soon.9. As you press each song, you'll hear a snippet of it play, so you can decide if it works. If it does, press the green W icon again. 10. Wombo will now work its Al-powered magic on the image, while telling you it is Transmitting particles through
radio waves and Uploading psychic connection to the reality plane. It isn't.11. Finally, the app will serve up your finished video. You'll have the option to save it to your device (as an mp4 file), share it
with a friend via any of the usual options (social media, WhatsApp, email and so on) or try again with
another image.

items.title: Wombo uses Al to make your selfies sing
items.description:
Wombo uses Al to make your selfies sing If you've ever wondered what Vladimir Putin singing Vengaboys' Boom, Boom, Boom, Boom! would look
like, this new deepfake-style lip-syncing app will show you.Wombo uses Al to animate photos so it appears they're singing along to one of 18 pop hits. Though designed for selfies, the app has gone viral over the past few days as users realized the comic
potential in uploading photos of famous people and making them sing along to entirely unsuitable
material
